abstract_ssm: The Visiting Nurse Association of Brooklyn was a charitable organization that provided home health service for residents of Brooklyn, New York. The collection consists of annual reports (1919-1935, 1962) and a program and seating list of the Diamond Jubilee Dinner Dance (1963).
